olive oil
1 parsnip
½ onion
1 packet peeled pumpkin pieces
½ tin sweetcorn
1 packet chicken breast
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 packet Mango Mayonnaise
1 cucumber
1 sachet Mild Caribbean Jerk Seasoning
1 packet Ocean Spray Craisins

Preheat the oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Cut
the parsnip into bite-sized chunks. Cut the red
onion (see ingredients) into wedges. Place the
peeled & chopped pumpkin, parsnip and onion
on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, then
season with salt and pepper. Toss to coat and
spread out evenly. Roast until tender,
25-30 minutes.

TIP: If your oven tray is crowded, divide between
two trays.

While the veggies are roasting, drain the sweetcorn
(see ingredients). Roughly chop the cucumber.
Place your hand flat on top of each chicken breast
and slice through horizontally to make two thin
steaks. In a medium bowl, combine the mild
Caribbean jerk seasoning and a drizzle of olive
oil. Add the chicken and turn to coat. Set aside.

Heat a large frying pan over a high heat. Cook the
sweetcorn, tossing, until lightly charred,
5 minutes. Transfer to a large bowl.

TIP: Cover the pan with a lid if the corn kernels are
“popping” out.

Return the pan to a medium-high heat with a
drizzle of olive oil. Cook the chicken until cooked
through, 3-5 minutes each side (cook in batches
if your pan is getting crowded). Transfer to a plate
to rest.

TIP: The spice blend will char in the pan – don't
worry, this adds to the flavour!

TIP: The chicken is cooked through when it's no
longer pink inside.

While the chicken is cooking, add the roasted
veggies, baby spinach leaves, Ocean Spray
craisins and cucumber to the charred corn.
Season to taste and toss to combine.

Slice the Caribbean chicken. Divide the roast
veggie toss between plates and top with the
chicken, spooning over any resting juices.
Serve with the mango mayonnaise.